text.section:
If the title to a severed mineral interest is vested in an unknown or missing owner, the circuit court of the county where the severed mineral interest is located may on petition, and after notice and a hearing:
Place the severed mineral interest in trust by order;
Appoint a trustee for the unknown or missing owner;
Order the trustee to create a separate trust bank account to manage all trust assets;
Authorize the trustee to sell, execute, and deliver a valid lease on the minerals to the owner of the surface estate; and
Place conditions on the authorization in item (4) of this subsection.

section.section:
The petition in paragraph (1) of this subsection shall:
Name as defendants:
The surface owners; and
Any other person with a legal interest in the severed mineral interest, including any unknown or missing owners; and
Include:
A legal description of the severed mineral interest;
A description of the putative property interests of each of the parties;
The last known address of each of the parties;
An affidavit signed by the surface owners, affirming fee simple ownership of the surface estate or estates, and requesting the court to convey title to the severed mineral interest at issue; and
An affidavit signed by the trustee, affirming that after conducting a diligent inquiry, including a search in the county where the severed mineral interest is located, performed in accordance with generally accepted standards of title examination of the land records of the county, records of register of wills of the county, and records of the circuit court for the county, the trustee cannot locate the unknown or missing owner.

text.section:
If the court orders the conveyance in accordance with subsection (d) of this section, the trustee shall:
Convey by recordable instrument the unknown or missing owner's severed mineral interest to the named surface owners;
Pay from any trust account all required taxes, court costs, expenses, and fees, including any fee for services to the trustee authorized by the court;
Pay any balance remaining in any trust account after the payments set forth in item (2) of this subsection to the named surface owners;
Close any trust account; and
Make a final report to the court accounting for the financial transactions of the trust.
